    },
    "body": "Callers building a block locator from a stale tip currently have to walk back one entry at a time using btck_block_tree_entry_get_previous. For large step sizes this means hundreds of C API calls per locator entry.\r\n\r\nThis exposes GetAncestor via btck_block_tree_entry_get_ancestor, which uses the existing CBlockIndex skiplist to reach any ancestor height in O(log N) and works on any chain, not just the active chain.\r\n\r\nIncludes a C++ convenience wrapper and tests covering same-height, genesis, and out-of-range cases.\r\n\r\nSee previous discussion here #34843\r\n\r\n\r\n",
